The aggregated compensation benchmarks published by The Healthcare Executive Compensation Project (percentile
statistics, prevalence rates, trend data, and downloadable data exports)
are licensed under the Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International
License.

You are free to:
  - Share — copy and redistribute the data in any medium or format
  - Adapt — remix, transform, and build upon the data for any purpose,
    including commercial use

Under the following terms:
  - Attribution — You must give appropriate credit (e.g., "Source:
    The Healthcare Executive Compensation Project, healthcomp.org"), provide a link to the license, and
    indicate if changes were made.

Full text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/

================================================================================
3. RAW SUBMISSIONS — Not Licensed
================================================================================

Individual, raw survey submissions are NOT covered by either license above.
Raw submissions are stored securely and never published, shared, or made
available in any form. They are used solely to compute the aggregated
benchmarks described in section 2.

This distinction exists to protect respondent anonymity. Even with
anonymization, individual-level compensation records could potentially be
re-identified when combined with external data. Only aggregated statistics
that meet minimum threshold requirements (5+ submissions, no single source
>25%) are ever published.
